A court in Meru has released a man on a Sh100 bail for stealing 15 passion fruits worth Sh60.Augustine Mwenda denied the charge and told Meru Principal Magistrate Monica Maroro that he was given the fruits by Evangeline Kamiri on Saturday in Magundu Village. The owner told me to collect the passion fruits that had fallen down from the tree, Mr Mwenda said.The case will be heard on October 17. email print email print The High Court in Nairobi has issued temporary orders blocking an impeachment motion against The note containing the threat was given to his driver by an unknown motorcycle rider.